60.4	RoboCop	RoboCop	RoboCop is a 1987 American science fiction action film directed by Paul Verhoeven. Set in a crime-ridden Detroit, Michigan in the near future, RoboCop centers on a police officer who is brutally murdered and subsequently re-created as a super-human cyborg known as "RoboCop". The film features Peter Weller, Dan O'Herlihy, Kurtwood Smith, Nancy Allen, Miguel Ferrer, and Ronny Cox.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/5/50/Robocop_film.jpg/220px-Robocop_film.jpg
